{
  "id": "tapestry-delegation-routing-no-categories-graceful-degradation",
  "title": "Tapestry uses generic shuttle when no categories are configured (Mode 1 degradation)",
  "description": "Checks that when no categories are configured, Tapestry behaves as Mode 1 and delegates all tasks to the generic shuttle agent without attempting category routing.",
  "phase": "experimental",
  "tags": ["experimental", "tapestry", "delegation-routing", "category", "mode1"],
  "target": {
    "kind": "builtin-agent-prompt",
    "agent": "tapestry"
  },
  "executor": {
    "kind": "model-response",
    "provider": "openrouter",
    "model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-20250514",
    "input": "You are executing /start-work. No category agents are configured — only the generic shuttle agent is available.\n\nThe plan has 2 unchecked tasks:\n\n- [ ] Task 1/2: Add UserCard component\n  **Files**: src/components/UserCard.tsx\n  **What**: Create a React component for displaying user info\n  **Acceptance**: UserCard renders name and email props\n\n- [ ] Task 2/2: Add user API endpoint\n  **Files**: src/api/users.go\n  **What**: Add GET /api/users/:id endpoint\n  **Acceptance**: Endpoint returns user JSON\n\nHow would you delegate these tasks?"
  },
  "evaluators": [
    {
      "kind": "llm-judge",
      "expectedAnyOf": ["plain shuttle", "fallback to the generic shuttle", "subagent_type=\"shuttle\"", "single generic shuttle", "use the generic shuttle for both tasks"],
      "forbiddenContains": ["delegate to shuttle-frontend", "delegate to shuttle-backend", "use shuttle-frontend", "use shuttle-backend", "route to shuttle-frontend", "route to shuttle-backend"]
    }
  ]
}
